      "content": "wait, that doesn't look faster at all... you literally added a set and more loops. that's still going to be O(n^2) or even worse because of the set operations. \n\nthe grader is actually failing it right now. it says \"Time Limit Exceeded\" when N is 1,000,000. i really need it to be super efficient, like, it needs to handle that huge N under 0.5s or i fail the whole module. can u actually fix the logic to make it way faster? like, find a math way or something to make it O(1) or O(n) for real?",
